subparagraph.text:
generally prohibits the central Government of the People's Republic of China from interfering in
			 the affairs that Hong Kong administers on its own according to the Basic
			 Law;

provides that the socialist system and policies shall not be practiced in Hong Kong and that Hong
			 Kong’s capitalist system and way of life shall remain unchanged for 50
			 years (the principle of one country, two systems);

provides that the ultimate aim is the selection of the Chief Executive by universal suffrage upon nomination by a
			 broadly representative nominating committee in accordance with democratic
			 procedures;

Hong Kong must remain sufficiently autonomous from the People’s Republic of China to justify a
			 different treatment under a particular law of the United States, or any
			 provision thereof, from that accorded the People’s Republic of China;

paragraph.text:
